    "content": "nullSalesforce B2B Commerce and D2C Commerce\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Salesforce B2B Commerce and D2C Commerce\n Commerce Basics\n Get Started with Salesforce Commerce\n Import and Export Commerce Data\n Access to Commerce Stores\n Products and Pricing\n Configure Checkout for a Commerce Store\n Store Search\n Search Engine Optimization (SEO) for Commerce\n Commerce Einstein\n Einstein and Data Usage in Commerce Cloud\n Data Cloud for Commerce\n Store Management\n Commerce Promotions\n Considerations for Commerce Promotions\n Configure a Promotion\n Create a Promotion\n Create a Promotion Using a Template\n Create Promotions with Einstein\n Target Customers with a Promotion Segment\n Add a Promotion Tier\n Create a Coupon\n Define a Promotion Discount\n Choose What Qualifies for a Promotion\n Set Conditional Rules for a Promotion\n Localize Promotion Data\n Customize Promotions in Experience Builder\n Promotions in Checkout for B2B (Aura) Stores\n Example Promotions\n Prioritizing Promotions\n Remove a Promotion\n Sell Globally\n Website Design for Commerce Stores\n Publication and Activation\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nB2B COMMERCE AND D2C COMMERCE\nCreate a Promotion\n\nWhen you create a base promotion, you can activate immediately or at a later time.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS\nAvailable in: Lightning Experience\nAvailable in: Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer Editions\nAvailable in: B2B Commerce and D2C Commerce\nIMPORTANT As of Summer ’24, there’s a refreshed Commerce app, which we encourage you to use. The navigation steps in this Help documentation reflect the new app. If you’re still using the previous app, now called the Commerce Storefront Console, see B2B and D2C Commerce Using the Commerce Storefront Console. For instructions on switching to the refreshed app, see Enable the Refreshed Commerce App.\nIn the navigation sidebar, select a store from the Store dropdown.\nClick Promotions.\nClick New.\nAdd the promotion details.\nFor Name, enter the internal name for your promotion.\nFor Display Name, enter a name that customers see in the cart when the promotion is in effect.\nIf you leave it blank, customers don’t know what discount they receive.\nEnter a priority number.\nThe priority number determines which promotions apply first. The lower the number, the higher the priority. If you don’t enter a priority number, or if two applied promotions have the same priority, prioritization tiebreaker rules apply. See Promotion Prioritization.\nIf you want to use qualifiers, from the Qualifier Criteria dropdown, select which qualifiers to apply: Any or All.\nTo activate the promotion as soon as you save it, select Active.\nTo improve performance, we recommend activating and prioritizing only the promotions that you’re using. When a customer adds products to the cart, Salesforce evaluates the first 50 active manual promotions and the first 50 active automatic promotions for their account to determine if they apply.\nSelect Commerce Promotion.\nTo combine the promotion with other promotions, for Exclusivity Type, select No.\nTo prevent combining the promotion with promotions of the same class (for example, you want one product promotion per product or one transaction promotion per order), select Class. To let it be the only promotion used for an entire order, select Global. To use the default setting (Class), select –None–. See Promotion Prioritization.\nEnter the terms and conditions, which you can choose to show in the cart.\nTo localize the promotion display name and terms and conditions, use the Translation Workbench. See Translation Workbench.\nSelect whether to exclude qualifying items from discounts.\nSelect when to start and end the promotion.\nAdd promotion type details.\nTo have the promotion automatically apply when qualifiers are met, select Automatic. If you’re requiring a coupon code, don’t select Automatic.\nIf there are no qualifiers, the promotion applies only when eligible targets are in the cart.\nTo make it a tiered promotion, select Tiered Promotion.\nThis setting is permanent and can’t be changed after you save the promotion. See Add a Promotion Tier.\nAdd the redemption details. Enter the maximum number of times that the promotion can apply to a cart. The default is 1.\nSave your work.\nEXAMPLE To help your customers through the upcoming heat wave, you want to hold a sale on cooling units next week. You have a summer general sale in progress, but you want to prioritize the cooling unit promotion. When you add a promotion:\nFor Priority Number, enter 1.\nMake sure that your other active promotions have a lower priority number.\nSelect Active.\nEnter when to start and end the promotion.\nTo apply the discount when the customer adds an eligible cooling unit to their cart, select Automatic.\nSEE ALSO\nManage Promotions with the Promotion Workspace\nCommerce Promotions\nAdd a Promotion Tier\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
